{"type":"message","id":"2ff561e1","parentId":"efee3dc9","timestamp":"2026-06-02T04:04:43.131Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a cron job trigger asking me to send a message to \"宋阿姨\" (Aunt Song). The message is about a dream about Bebop's kitchen having a cup of tea, similar to one she was supposed to bring.\n\nSince this is a QQ bot channel, I need to send this message through the QQ channel. Let me look at the context - the current channel is qqbot, so I should reply with the message content which will be delivered to the user automatically. Actually, let me check if there's a specific way to send a message to a specific person.\n\nLooking at the cron job details, this is a push-urge type job. The instruction says \"if you do not send directly, your final plain-text reply will be delivered automatically.\" So I should just reply with the message content.\n\nBut wait - \"发一条消息给宋阿姨\" means send a message to Aunt Song. In the QQ bot context, I'm not sure if my reply goes to a specific person or to the channel. Let me just compose the message as requested.\n\nThe message to send:\n\"宋阿姨，我梦见Bebop号的厨房里有一杯茶。跟你说要给我带的那杯一样的。\"\n\nThis is a casual, warm message to Aunt Song. I'll just output it as my reply.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"宋阿姨，我梦见Bebop号的厨房里有一杯茶。跟你说要给我带的那杯一样的。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"deepseek","model":"deepseek-v4-flash","usage":{"input":8294,"output":292,"cacheRead":2432,"cacheWrite":0,"reasoningTokens":268,"totalTokens":11018,"cost":{"input":0.00116116,"output":0.00008176,"cacheRead":0.00006809599999999999,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.001311016}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780373076541,"responseId":"7e0436a8-8784-4b7b-a251-d35ec4beb1f1"}}
